GET_ROTATION_TOOLTIP: Finds the rotation (in degrees) of a Game Object.
ROTATE_TOOLTIP: Rotates a game object by the given angle in degrees. Negative numbers will rotate it the opposite direction.
SET_ROTATION_TOOLTIP: Directly sets the rotation (in degrees) of this game object to the given value.
GET_LOCAL_BOUNDS_TOOLTIP: Gets the rectangular bounds of an object. Bounds are relative to the object itself instead of the world.
RESET_TOOLTIP: Gets most objects ready to play again in various ways and treats it like new. Specifically, moves it to a new position then makes sure it is visible, rendering, alive, and actually exists in the game world.
REVIVE_TOOLTIP: Brings a 'dead' Game Object back to life. Makes sure it counts as alive, existing, and visible. Will send an event named onRevived.
ADD_TEXT_TOOLTIP: Add text to the screen at the specified location
SET_TEXT_TOOLTIP: Sets what phaser text will display on the screen.
SET_TEXT_VI_TOOLTIP: Sets what phaser text will display on the screen.
CREATE_BITMAPFONT_TOOLTIP: Loads a font into the game. These don't work like normal fonts. See the help for more info.
DRAWCIRCLE_TOOLTIP: Draws a circle at a given position in the world. Doesn't work on its own. Put it inside the 'fill shapes with' block.
GET_OBJECT_WIDTH_TOOLTIP: Gets the width of an object.
SET_OBJECT_WIDTH_TOOLTIP: Sets the width of an object.
EMITTER_MAKE_PARTICLES_TOOLTIP: Generate a new set of particles for this emitter
EMITTERS_MAKE_PARTICLES_TOOLTIP: Generate a new set of particles for this emitter
EMITTERS_SET_ROTATION_TOOLTIP: Set the angular velocity constraints of the particles
EMITTERS_SET_ROTATION_VI_TOOLTIP: Set the angular velocity constraints of the particles.
EMITTERS_SET_ALPHA_TOOLTIP: Set the min and max alpha values for this emitter.
EMITTERS_SET_ALPHA_VI_TOOLTIP: Set the min and max alpha values for this emitter.
EMITTERS_SET_SCALE_TOOLTIP: Set the minimum/maximum scale for particles and the rate to go between.
EMITTERS_SET_SCALE_VI_TOOLTIP: Set the minimum/maximum scale for particles and the rate to go between.
SET_EMIT_FROM_TOOLTIP: Set where the particles emit from, by individual coordinate.
EMITTERS_SET_SPEED_TOOLTIP: Sets the minimum and maximum speeds that an emitted particle will go.
EMITTERS_SET_SPEED_VI_TOOLTIP: Sets the minimum and maximum speeds that an emitted particle will go.
EMITTERS_SET_GRAVITY_TOOLTIP: Set the gravity of generated particles.
EMITTERS_SET_GRAVITY_VI_TOOLTIP: Set the gravity of generated particles
EMITTERS_SET_WIDTH_TOOLTIP: Sets the width of the area in which particles will be emitted.
DEBUG_SPRITE_TOOLTIP: Draws various information useful for debugging about the specified sprite at the given world coordinates.
STATEMANAGER_ADD_STATE_TOOLTIP: Adds a state to the game engine, this should be an instance of a state class.
STATEMANAGER_START_STATE_TOOLTIP: Start the specified state, this should be a state that has been added to the game engine
RECTANGLE_CREATE_TOOLTIP: Defines a rectangle, can be used for cropping, alignment and other tasks
POINT_CREATE_TOOLTIP: Defines a point which represents a location in 2D
POINT_GET_ELEMENT_TOOLTIP: Defines a point which represents a location in 2D
POINT_SET_ELEMENT_TOOLTIP: Defines a point which represents a location in 2D
POINT_SET_MAGNITUDE_TOOLTIP: Sets the magnitude of the point
POINTS_ADD_TOOLTIP: Adds the two points and returns the result
POINTS_SUBTRACT_TOOLTIP: Adds the two points and returns the result
POINTS_ANGLE_BETWEEN_TOOLTIP: Returns the angle in radians between the two point objects
POINTS_DISTANCE_TOOLTIP: Returns the distance between the two point objects
POINTS_DIVIDE_TOOLTIP: Returns a new point p = [a.x / b.x, a.y / b.y]
POINTS_EQUALS_TOOLTIP: Determines if two points are equal
POINTS_INTERPOLATE_TOOLTIP: Interpolate between two points, the percent (0.0 - 1.0) determines how far towards the second point (1 - F) * A + F * B
POINTS_PERPENDICULAR_TOOLTIP: Find a perpendicular vector to this point
CAMERA_FOLLOW_VI_TOOLTIP: Make the camera follow the specified game object
CAMERA_FADE_TOOLTIP: Fades the screen to the specified colour over time. Ends with the screen completely obscured.
CAMERA_FLASH_TOOLTIP: Immediately covers the camera with the specified colour. Then fades back in over a given time. Useful for fading back in after fading out, or as a big hit effect.
CAMERA_FOCUS_ON_TOOLTIP: Immediately centers the camera on the specified game object.
CAMERA_FOCUS_ON_XY_TOOLTIP: Immediately centers the camera on a given position.
CAMERA_RESET_TOOLTIP: Completely resets the camera. It goes back to (0, 0), stops following anything, and removes all effects such as shake or flash.
CAMERA_RESET_FX_TOOLTIP: Removes visual effects from the camera such as fading in/out. Does not affect the position, follow target, or screen shake.
CAMERA_SET_BOUNDS_TO_WORLD_FIELD_1: set camera bounds to world bounds
CAMERA_SET_BOUNDS_TO_WORLD_TOOLTIP: The camera bounds are not the size of what it shows, but the space it can move around in. This sets those bounds so that the camera can view the entire world, but nothing more.
CAMERA_SET_POSITION_TOOLTIP: Jumps the camera immediately to the given position. Note that the camera's position is its upper left corner, not its center.
CAMERA_SET_SIZE_TOOLTIP: Sets the size of the camera's view window.
CAMERA_SHAKE_TOOLTIP: Screen shake. Great for impact effects, or just a little extra umph, but don't go overboard. The intensity goes from 0 to 1. % of bounds it can move
CAMERA_UNFOLLOW_TOOLTIP: Makes the camera stop following anything. Equivalent to making the camera follow null.
CAMERA_FOLLOW_VI_STYLED_TOOLTIP: Make the camera follow the specified game object
SET_SOUND_BOOLEAN_MEMBER_TOOLTIP: Set the selected member on the Sound
GET_SOUND_BOOLEAN_MEMBER_TOOLTIP: Get the selected member from the Sound
SET_SOUND_NUMERIC_MEMBER_TOOLTIP: Set the selected member on the Sound
GET_SOUND_NUMERIC_MEMBER_TOOLTIP: Get the selected member from the Sound
GET_SOUND_STRING_MEMBER_TOOLTIP: Get the selected member from the Sound
LOAD_SOUND_TOOLTIP: Loads an audio file so you can use it later. The tag is a name you use to access it later. The source is a file path. URLs work as a source too, but this is not recommended.
ADD_SOUND_TOOLTIP: Add a Sound to the game
PLAY_SOUND_TOOLTIP: Plays a sound that has been created. The volume goes from 0 to 1.
REMOVE_SOUND_TOOLTIP: Stops all sounds with the given tag.
STOP_PAUSE_RESUME_SOUNDS_TOOLTIP: Stop - Stop everything dead. Pause - Stop everything, but remember where you were. Resume - Start playing paused sounds from where they left off.
SOUND_FADE_IN_TOOLTIP: Starts/Restarts the sound sets the volume to zero and increases from 0 to 1 over duration
SOUND_FADE_OUT_TOOLTIP: Fades the sounds volume to 0 over the given duration
SOUND_FADE_TO_TOOLTIP: Fades the sounds volume to a given volume over the given duration
LIST_FIND_CLOSEST_TOOLTIP: Returns the value closest to the given number in a sorted, numeric list. If two values are equally close, it returns the higher one.
LIST_GET_RANDOM_TOOLTIP: Returns a random item from the given list.
NUMBER_LIST_FIELD_1: create a list with every number from
NUMBER_LIST_TOOLTIP: Creates a list of numbers, in order within the specified range, including the start and end.
NUMBER_LIST_STEP_TOOLTIP: Creates a list in the given range, counting up by a specified value. Does NOT include the end of the range.
LIST_REMOVE_RANDOM_ITEM_FIELD_1: get and remove a random item from
LIST_REMOVE_RANDOM_ITEM_TOOLTIP: Removes a random item from a list and returns it. Note that this modifies the list.
LIST_SHUFFLE_TOOLTIP: Randomly rearranges the order of items in a list. Works for more than just cards.
RANDOM_ANGLE_TOOLTIP: Returns a random angle between -180 and 180.
RANDOM_PICK_TOOLTIP: Returns a random member in a given list.
RANDOM_PICK_WEIGHTED_TOOLTIP: Returns a random member in a given list. This version chooses items close to the start of the list more frequently.
RANDOM_REAL_TOOLTIP: Returns a random real number. This can be anywhere between 0 and 2^32 (about 4 billion).
RANDOM_REAL_IN_RANGE_TOOLTIP: Returns a random real number in the specified range.
RANDOM_SIGN_TOOLTIP: Returns either +1 or -1. For deciding if something needs to be positive or negative.
MATH_DEG_TO_RAD_TOOLTIP: Converts a value in degrees to an equivalent in radians.
MATH_RAD_TO_DEG_TOOLTIP: Converts an angle in degrees to an equivalent in radians.
DIGITALWRITE_TOOLTIP: Writes either HIGH or LOW to the given pin
DIGITAL_READ_TOOLTIP: Reads either HIGH or LOW from a digital pin
ANALOG_REFERENCE_TOOLTIP: Set the reference voltage for analog input
ANALOG_READ_TOOLTIP: Read the value from the given analog pin
SERVO_CANNOT_BE_NULL: servo field cannot be left empty
ARDUINO_SERIAL_AVAILABLE_TOOLTIP: Gets the number of bytes available to be read
ARDUINO_SERIAL_AVAILABLE_FOR_WRITE_TOOLT: Gets the number of bytes available to write
ARDUINO_SERIAL_FIND_TOOLTIP: Returns true if the target string is found in the serial stream else false
ARDUINO_SERIAL_FIND_UNTIL_TOOLTIP: Returns true if the target string is found in the serial stream else false if timeout or terminal is found
ARDUINO_SERIAL_FLUSH_TOOLTIP: wait fo outgoing serial data to complete
ARDUINO_SERIAL_PARSE_FLOAT_TOOLTIP: read the first valid float form the serial stream
ARDUINO_SERIAL_PARSE_INT_TOOLTIP: read the first valid integer form the serial stream
ARDUINO_SERIAL_PEEK_TOOLTIP: gets the next byte without removing it from the stream
ARDUINO_SERIAL_READ_BYTES_TOOLTIP: gets the next byte without removing it from the stream
ARDUINO_SERIAL_READ_BYTES_UNTIL_TOOLTIP: gets the next byte without removing it from the stream
ARDUINO_SERIAL_SET_TIMEOUT_TOOLTIP: sets the max milliseconds to wait for serial data, defaults to 1000 milliseconds
ADVANCED_IO_PULSE_IN_TOOLTIP: Reads a HIGH or LOW pulse from a pin returning the duration
ADVANCED_IO_PULSE_IN_LONG_TOOLTIP: Reads a HIGH or LOW pulse from a pin returning the duration
ADVANCED_IO_SHIFT_IN_TOOLTIP: Shifts in a byte of data at a time, this is software based
ADVANCED_IO_SHIFT_OUT_TOOLTIP: Shifts out a byte of data at a time, this is software based
ADD_EVENT_LISTENER_TITLE: add event listener to dom element
JAVASCRIPT_EVAL_OUTPUT_TOOLTIP: Execute the JavaScript expression returning the value
RANDOM_EYES_FIELD_1: Set Eyes To A Random Colour
HARDWARESTARTUP_TOOLTIP: This code is run once when the device is first turned on
LOOP_TOOLTIP: This code is run continuously once the device is turned on
ACCELERATEMOTORS_TOOLTIP: Accelerates from the start to the end speed over the specified duration
MOTORS_TOOLTIP: Sets the motor speed to something positive or negative for both the left and right motor
SPINLEFT_TOOLTIP: Spins the wink robot to the left
SPINRIGHT_TOOLTIP: Spins the wink robot to the right
BESTILL_TOOLTIP: Stops the wink robot from moving
BUTTONWAIT_TOOLTIP: Waits until a remote button is pressed to continue.
BEEPON_TOOLTIP: Turns on the beep until it's told to stop;
SET_LEFT_EYE_TOOLTIP: Sets the color of the left eye.
SET_RIGHT_EYE_TOOLTIP: Sets the color of the right eye.
SET_EYES_TOOLTIP: Sets the color of both eyes.
BUTTON_PRESSED_TOOLTIP: Gets the remote button that was pressed.
TURN_BY_VALUES_TOOLTIP: Turns the robot at the specified speed for the specified duration in the specified direction - either left or right. Negative values are accepted.
RESTART_IR_TOOLTIP: Start listening for IR should be setup and in loop after processing an input
IS_IR_DONE_TOOLTIP: Checks to see if we received an IR input to process
IR_CONTROL_CONTAINER_TOOLTIP: Code starts running from here when IR data is done being recieved.
IR_CONTROL_CONTROL_TOOLTIP: Check to see what key was pressed
DELTA_TIME_SECONDS_TOOLTIP: Get the time elapsed since the last frame in seconds.
DELTA_TIME_MILLISECONDS_TOOLTIP: Get the time elapsed since the last frame in milliseconds.
GET_TIME_NUMERIC_MEMBER_TOOLTIP: Read numeric fields of game time.
SET_TIME_NUMERIC_MEMBER_TOOLTIP: Write to one of the game time's numeric fields.
CREATE_TIMER_TOOLTIP: Create a new timer, if auto destroy is true this timer will be destoryed after all events are dispatched
TIMER_CONSTANTS_TOOLTIP: Constants for some common values in milliseconds
START_TIMER_TOOLTIP: Start timer after a given delay in milliseconds
TIMER_ADD_EVENT_TOOLTIP: Fire the event after the specified delay after the start of the timer
DESTROY_TIMER_TOOLTIP: destroys the timer andy pending events are not dispatched
TIMER_LOOP_EVENT_TOOLTIP: Loops the given event forever or until the timer is stopped or destroyed
TIMER_REPEAT_EVENT_TOOLTIP: Loops the given event forever or until the timer is stopped or destroyed
PAUSE_TIMER_TOOLTIP: Pauses the timer and all events in the queue
RESUME_TIMER_TOOLTIP: Resumes the timer and all events in the queue
STOP_TIMER_TOOLTIP: Stops the timer and all events in the queue, if auto destroy is true this will not cause it to be destroyed
TIMER_SET_ON_COMPLETE_CALLBACK_TOOLTIP: Called when the timer completes all of the actions in its queue. This will not be called if the timer is stopped or destroyed before it completes its queue.
PHASER_EASING_TOOLTIP: Prebuilt easing functions you can utilize through out your code
PHASER_GAME_ADD_TWEEN_TO_TOOLTIP: Create a tween from the current value to the end values
PHASER_GAME_ADD_TWEEN_FROM_TOOLTIP: Create a tween from the end value to the current values, setting the values to end first
PHASER_TWEEN_MUTATORCONTAINER_TOOLTIP: List of properties to tween on the target object
PHASER_TWEEN_MUTATORARG_TOOLTIP: Property to tween on the target object
PHASER_STOP_TWEEN_TOOLTIP: Stop the tween dispatching onComplete if complete is checked
PHASER_PAUSE_TWEEN_TOOLTIP: pause the tween dispatching onComplete if complete is checked
PHASER_START_TWEEN_TOOLTIP: start the tween dispatching onComplete if complete is checked
PHASER_RESUME_TWEEN_TOOLTIP: resume the tween dispatching onComplete if complete is checked
PHASER_YOYO_TWEEN_TOOLTIP: enable or disable yoyoing for this tween
SECONDS_SINCE_START_TOOLTIP: Gets the number of seconds since start of the program.
MILLISECONDS_SINCE_START_TOOLTIP: Gets the number of milliseconds since start of the program. There are 1,000 milliseconds in a second.
MICROSECONDS_SINCE_START_TOOLTIP: Gets the number of microseconds since start of the program. There are 1,000,000 microseconds in a second.
DELAY_SECONDS_TOOLTIP: Wait the specified number of seconds before continuing with the program.
DELAY_MILLISECONDS_TOOLTIP: Wait the specified number of milliseconds before continuing. There are 1,000 milliseconds in a second.
DELAY_MICROSECONDS_TOOLTIP: Wait the specified number of microseconds before continuing. There are 1,000,000 microseconds in a second.
WINK_MOVEMENT_FORWARD_SLOW: Moves the wink robot forward at a slow(30) speed.
WINK_MOVEMENT_FORWARD_MODERATE: Moves the wink robot forward at a moderate(50) speed.
WINK_MOVEMENT_FORWARD_FAST: Moves the wink robot forward at a fast(90) speed.
WINK_MOVEMENT_BACKWARD_SLOW: Moves the wink robot backward at a slow(30) speed.
WINK_MOVEMENT_BACKWARD_MODERATE: Moves the wink robot backward at a moderate(50) speed.
WINK_MOVEMENT_BACKWARD_FAST: Moves the wink robot backward at a fast(90) speed.
WINK_MOVEMENT_ROTATION_LEFT: Rotates the wink robot left by roughly the specified number of degrees.
WINK_MOVEMENT_ROTATION_RIGHT: Rotates the wink robot right by roughly the specified number of degrees.
LIGHT_EFFECT_POLICE_LIGHTS: Makes the eyes flash red and blue for the specified time in seconds.
LIGHT_EFFECT_DISCO_LIGHTS: Makes the eyes twinkle with blues, greens, and purples for the specified time in seconds.
LIGHT_EFFECT_FIREWORK_LIGHTS: Makes the eyes flicker as if a firework had gone off for the specified time in seconds.
LIGHT_EFFECT_RAINBOW_LIGHT: Makes the eyes cycle through the rainbow for the specified time in seconds.
SENSOR_LINE_FOLLOW_TOOLTIP: Wink robot will follow a black line. For best results, use a solid dark line 3/4cm - 1cm thick on white paper.
SENSOR_LINE_AVOID_TOOLTIP: Wink robot will avoid black lines. For best results, use solid lines at least 1/2cm thick or more on white paper.
SENSOR_OBSTACLE_AVOID_TOOLTIP: Wink robot travels around and attempts to avoid obstacles in front of it.
SENSOR_OBSTACLE_APPROACH_TOOLTIP: Wink robot approaches an obstacle placed in front of it then moved.

WINK_EYE_RIGHT_CYAN: Sets the right eye to be cyan with the specified intensity
WINK_EYE_RIGHT_ORANGE: Sets the right eye to be orange with the specified intensity
WINK_EYE_RIGHT_WHITE: Sets the right eye to be white with the specified intensity
WINK_EYE_RIGHT_SELECT: Sets the right eye to be the specified color with max intensity.
WINK_EYE_RIGHT_RGB: Sets the right eye to be the specified Red, Green, and Blue values.

WINK_EYES_BOTH_GREEN: Sets both eyes to be green with the specified intensity
WINK_EYES_BOTH_BLUE: Sets both eyes to be blue with the specified intensity
WINK_EYES_BOTH_PURPLE: Sets both eyes to be purple with the specified intensity
WINK_EYES_BOTH_PINK: Sets both eyes to be pink with the specified intensity

GAME_CAMERA_TOOLTIP: reference to the current games camera
STATEMANAGER_RESTART_STATE_TOOLTIP: Restarts the current State. State.shutDown will be called (if it exists) before the State is restarted.
STATEMANAGER_CHECK_STATE_TOOLTIP: Returns if a given phaser state is valid. A State is considered valid if it has at least one of the core functions: preload, create, update or render.
